Hi

Usually with JUnit you test all your public methods.  But you don&#39;t have
any, apart from your constructors.  And since there aren&#39;t any getter
methods for your fields you can&#39;t inspect them after you constructed your
object.  Therefore the best JUnit test you could do is to instantiate your
object and check that no exceptions are thrown.  You should check out
www.junit.org to read more about getting started with Junit.

A member of the group, Johannes I believe, uploaded this great chapter about
GUI testing.  After you have got started with Junit you should read it
(http://groups.yahoo.com/group/junit/files/UnitTestingInJava-chap13-GUITesti
ng.pdf) it will definitely help you with your testing.  I helped me (thanks
Johannes).

Good luck, James

